<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She may have been surrounded by glamorous A-listers, but Princess Charlene of Monaco proved she was clearly the star of the show at the Monte-Carlo Gala for Planetary Health tonight.</p>

<p>The royal mother-of-two, 42, arrived alongside her husband Prince Albert, 62, when appearing at the star-studded event, which aims to highlight the idea that our future is dependent on healthy ecosystems.</p>

<p>Looking effortlessly elegant, Charlene sported a floor-length silver gown to the occasion - which also included guests such as American actress Rebel Wilson and English film star Helen Mirren.</p>

<p>Hosted by the Prince Albert II of Monaco Foundation, the annual event gathers leading philanthropists, talents and scientists to join forces and launch the charity's initiatives to bridge the widening gap between health and the environment.</p>

<p>She may have been surrounded by glamorous A-listers, but Princess Charlene of Monaco (pictured with her husband) proved she was clearly the star of the show at the Monte-Carlo Gala for Planetary Health tonight</p>

<p>The royal mother-of-two, 42, arrived alongside her husband Prince Albert (pictured), 62, when appearing at the star-studded event, which aims to highlight that our future is dependent on healthy ecosystems</p>

<p>Charlene's shimmering frock boasted a plunging neckline and a cinched-waist detailing to showcase her svelte frame.</p>

<p>The gown featured wide, long-sleeved arms to add to its elegance, while the royal teamed it with a dazzling open necklace and a silver facemask.</p>

<p>She kept her short locks straight and added a smattering of glamorous makeup to complete her stylish evening look.</p>

